  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON: The proposed first floor fascia sign, by reason of the positioning and method of internal illumination would have would have an adverse detrimental material effect on the visual amenity of the area and would undermine the coherence, integrity and quality of the building.  The proposal would therefore fail to preserve or enhance the character and appearance of the surrounding Mercers Road/ Tavistock Terrace conservation area. The proposal would therefore be contrary to the NPPF (2012); policy CS12 of the Core Strategy (2012); policies ENV11, D4, D11, D13, D19, D22 and D34 of the Islington Unitary Development Plan (2002); draft policies DM1, DM3 and DM6 and the guidance contained within Conservation Area Design Guide (2003), the Shopfront Design Guide (2003) and the Islington Urban Design Guide (2006)."
